values: HARRY IS MOVING BACK HOME TOMORROW!!!!!!! AHHHHHHHHHHHHH YAYYYYYYYYYYYYY :) :) :) :) :)

so basically i dont know why i decided to take summer classes because they SUCK!!!!!!!! my consumer behavior class i had a midterm (i got an 87 so it wasnt too bad) and now monday i have a 6-8 page paper and 7-8 minute presentation i have to do on the gay and lesbian subculture and their consumer behavior patterns like wtffffff! ive been procrastinating so its saturday and i only have 1/2 of it done and its due monday night... oh well... i just want this class to be over! and i have an english class and i have to do a 5-7 page paper on love and death from 3 stories and like how they compare and contrast...its so dumb! i didnt have any papers or presentations last semester...ahhhhhh its stressing me out! it is suppose to be summer and i should be at the beach but i am in my house working on this dumb thing!!! 

last night we went to devroe and went on the swings woooooo i love going there at night its so pretty and there were so many stars!!! hahahah i am such a geek! i wish harry was here because i would take him there and we could just get a blanket and cuddle and look at the stars and ocean hahahah wow im pretty gay, huh? oh well! :) 

speaking of harry... he seems to be doing good out there :) just working and hanging out...only a month a week until i go out there!!!! i am so excited!!!! hahahaha but its understandable... i havent seen him since march 18!!! wow that is like 3 months ago from today...it seems like forever though :( i need me some looloo hahahaha it hasnt been easy though...but now i know how it is to be in a long distance relationship...its all about trust big time...and that is a little bit hard for me, but he has never given me any reason to not trust him i just think waaaaaay too much i think...oh well im only human :)

cookout at my aunts today for fathers day... which basically means me, my bathing suit, a hot tub full of ice to make it cold hahaha, and some white russians NICEEEEEE :) 

party tonight, maybe? this could end up being very sketchy!!!!!

last week i took a week long class from 8:30-4:30 and then night class from 6:30-9:30... i have never been so worn out in my life... i will never EVER do that to myself again... i had a midterm on wednesday for the class, a final on friday, and i have a 5 page paper due on monday!!! i am so not in the mood to write it :( blahhhhhhhh its summer seriously! wtfffff! well i guess i have to do what i got to do in order to graduate in four years... 

and other than that nothing else is going on... sarahs 21 bday was on may 19th and we went into boston to fire and ice.. that was an adventure driving in there hahah we got lost going in and coming out but we made it home :) and now i dont really have anything to do...

im going insane from boredom!!! i hate massachusetts there is never anything good to do except drive around and eat and be fat seriously hahahah no wonder why this world is getting obese!!! thank god for TCBY hahaha that ice cream is wicked good! or should i say "frozen yogurt"...i wish sarah and amanda lived close to hang out but its alright ill see them at least a couple times this summer! trips to hampton beach wooooo (and hopefully i get over my fear of driving the highway! i HAVE to stop with that! it is a hugeeee fear, but i need to overcome it!)

im starting to miss harry like crazy :( this whole situation sucks balls hahaha but no really it does... like i havent seen him since march 18!!!!!!!! wtfffff is that???!?!? seriously im going through withdrawals...i think being in love is like being addicted to a drug it is so weird...not like i count or anything hahaha but its like 2 months and a week and i still have 2 MORE MONTHS!!! it sucks when you have a boyfriend but you cant see them or cuddle with them or hold hands with them or just sleep with them... it is a very weird situation...it feels like im with him, but im not? i have no idea... and all it is is constant worry, like i hope hes not out with another girl or i hope hes happy out there and i hope i make him happy, its just a lot of questions floating around in my head that wont go away as hard as i try to not think about it... i guess its human nature to worry about the things you have no control over...i think im just afraid of getting my heart broken, as cliche as that sounds...but i cant live my days thinking like that! i need to take each day at a time and do things for myself that i enjoy and that i find rewarding... i cant sit and worry it will take too much of the life im suppose to be living away from me...i need to stay happy and focused and soon everything will fall into place

wow i definitly havent written in this thing in soooo long!!! alot has happened the past couple months... first harry was home until the end of february so we got to spend our 1 year anniversary together and valentines day... but then he left to go back there february 26 :( but then i went to visit him in new mexico for my spring break!!! so technically we were only apart for like 2 weeks before i got to see him again :) i was there until march 17 (got my first facial ever and loved it lol) and ive been stuck here in this shithole since then... just working, going to school, going to gold's... just trying to keep myself busy and not think about the fact that i wont be seeing him again for another 3 months :( im going out to new mexico from july 27 to august 15 to visit... it should be a great time... but as of right now i hate the situation :( everyday im constantly reminded that im alone here, and the person who loves me and understands me the most is across the country...everyone keeps telling me "oh that must be so hard! you must miss him so much!" ok yes and yes...but dont sit there and keep saying that to me! it makes me miss him even more :( my friends sarah, amanda, and katie have been really good! they keep me busy and always find ways to just hang out and have girls nights...something ive been missing for the past year! its funny, you never realize how much you miss something until you go without it for so long...friday night im going up to sarah's house with amanda in amesbury to see her sister and friends before their prom :) that should be fun! and then we might drive around hampton beach and stuff our faces with junk food :) hahaha! only a week left of classes basically and then finals! sophomore year done and over with!! then im taking 3 summer classes (mgmt theory & prac, consumer behavior, and world lit II) that last until june 30... mgmt is a week long class, and consumer behavior is mw 6:30-9:30 and world lit II is tth 6:30-9:30...that should keep me busy until july :) my job is only giving me 10 hours a week, so basically i should look for another side job, like babysitting, or something i can be outside doing so i can get a decent tan hahah im taking a RAD class... tonight is fight night and we get to beat up the cops that teach the class hahah that should be interesting :) other then that...sarah is turning 21 may 19!!! that should be an interesting night... too bad everyone else is younger then her! i cant wait until summer :) trips to hampton beach, amandas house in the cape for the fourth of july...yayyy ive never been before! im wicked excited :).. road trips!! thats basically it :)

harry's back home :)

he flew in on friday and we went out to eat and got chinese food :) it was so weird not having him around! but on the other hand it was good too because i got to see people i haven't seen in awhile :) and i didnt go out to eat so i lost some weight hahah

today is our one year anniversary! he just surprised me at work with two dozen roses! one set of red ones and one set of pink ones :) they are sooo nice!! and he met the people i work with and ate the rest of my mom's dube's chicken hahah 

tonight we're going into boston to vinny testas or just staying around here and going out to dinner..i cant believe its already a year!! i made him a scrapbook so he can have it to remember stuff and to take out to new mexico when he moves out there at the end of february..

it is definitly going to suck trying to keep together a long distance relationship...but if its meant to be then it will work out! hes making really good money down there already and is already looking for his own apartment or condo! im so proud of him for taking this opportunity :) 

i have classes everyday this semester which sucks....so i go into class 8:30-2:20 on mondays and tues/thurs 8:30-1:45...wed/fri i go in 8:30-10:20 and then work 11-5..not too bad...bus calc, macroeconomics, and financial acct are already kicking my butt...i havent had so much homework in college yet! this semester is going to kill me...oh well!

im going to new mexico in march for spring break...and were going to mexico for 3 days!!! that should be interesting :) i need to start tanning im a ghost literally...im so pale its disgusting!

nail appt at 3:15 today yayyyy :)

went to new mexico for new years...

it was relaxing...we just hung out and went shopping and had some cookouts... we went to bill's parents house for new years eve and she cooked steak ( made chicken just for me because i hate steak hahah) and it was a nice meal...i kicked their butts in uno and we just had a good time :) me and harry went in their hot tub and just hung out...instead of saying happy new year at 12:00 out there we said it at 10:00 because when it was 10:00 out there it was really midnight at home :) 

harry was suppose to fly home with me on tuesday but he ended up staying in new mexico last minute to train for his new job out there...so i had to fly all the way home alone :( and there were delays in albuquerque and chicago! i got to the airport at 11am and didnt get home until midnight in boston!! 

thursday night i got pizza at little italy and watched sisterhood of the traveling pants with amanda! that was fun :) friday night sarah picked me up and i went to her house in amesbury and just hung out around her town...saturday i went to see memoirs of a geisha with jamie...that movie was really good!!! and sunday i just went to the gym and started making harry's scrapbook for our one year..

harry is suppose to fly home on friday but now he's saying he might not be home until february 1st??? :( i miss him alot...its going to stink next month when he actually moves there :(

but last night i bought tickets to go out there from march 11-march 18 during my spring break to go see him :) 

i hope this all works out between us... distance is a hard thing to work at :(

went to the patriots vs. tampa bay game on the 17th!!! it was soooo much fun!! i won raffle tickets at my work christmas party and they were club seats!! soo obviously i took harry and he was so surprised!! when i won them at work i didnt call him and tell him i waited until he came to my house...and i laid out a set of directions to the stadium that said turn over on the other side and said the game time and place and he was sooo excited!! he just kept smiling and couldnt stop lol so the seats we had were in the red seat section in between the 20 and 30 yard line and we had a place to go inside too! and there were huge bars set up and leather couches and seats and bar tables and chairs and the bathrooms were soo nice like a rich hotel lol it was so much fun! we both bought patriots jerseys the night before and wore them :)

harrys parents left the 20th for new mexico so we've been going back and forth staying at my house some of the time and his house the other half of the times...brad's home from the army so him, sean, nicole and steve came over harrys one night and we just hung out.. and we went christmas shopping with jimmy!

harry stayed over christmas eve and we opened presents together in the morning :) it was so much fun having someone else to open presents with instead of just me my mom my dad and mistletoe lol harry got me one of those workout balls i wanted, northface boots (for when i have to walk to school in the snow lol), a pink northface jacket with matching hat, scarf, and gloves because he wants me to go skiing with him, a pink water bottle, bath and body works stuff, and a soft big white christmas teddy bear! then we spent the rest of the day eating lunch at my house, then we stopped at his grandmother and aunts house! it was fun :) larry stopped by with jay christmas night because we havent really seen him since he moved to boston in november! he seems to be doing pretty good :) 

we leave friday for new mexico again!! it should be fun...i might try skiing and go with him and bill to a resort in colorado! i hope i dont break any bones or anything lol

back to work... which by the way they are keeping me so i will not be losing my job just yet :)

i really really really don't want harry to move to new mexico at the end of february :(

we're not breaking up, it's just going to be so hard not seeing him like i do now...

he's going out there for work...selling machines for food packaging companies, and he'll make a good salary plus commission off of all the machines he actually sells...but its still going to be hard..

ill go out to visit him for spring break in march...and then ill have school until probably almost july because im going to take a couple of summer courses so i can graduate faster and move out there with him...then maybe spend a month of summer out there?

ahh this is not going to be fun...

ill just keep myself busy with classes at the gym and maybe actually study, considering i decided to put business calculus, accounting, and macroeconomics all into one semester..good one danielle!

eh this sucks....

harry's sister just called him...

they're flying us down to new mexico for NEW YEARS WOOOOOOOOOOO :)

now its christmas with the pelletier's and new years with the lampes's!

new mexico was amazing!!! i can't believe i've been and im already back home!! kind of sucks being back here..but that's life i guess...

the first day we left at 1am to get the plane at 5:20...then we changed over in cincinnati and got to new mexico at 10am...me and katina went shopping and harry and bill went to work...then we went on this tramway up the mountains and had appetizers at the restaurant on top of the mountain...you could see the whole city from up there!! then we got dinner..i got chicken while everyone ate their huge steaks lol

thursday was thanksgiving...we went over around 2 so i spent the whole morning reading nicole ritchie's new book...i ended up finishing it before we left new mexico lol all about her life and drug problems...it was sort of interesting...thanksgiving was good..the usual turkey and mashed potatoes but she made sweet potato fluff with marshmellows ew and green bean caserole ew...i tried both by they were nasty...bill stuck the turkey neck in his pants and freaked me out because it really looked like his wang hahah..then bills sister jenny brought her mexican boyfriend for dinner, oh and she had to let us know he shot to people...awesome...he was like a 5'3 midget guy with fake gold jewelry everywhere...what a weirdo...then we went in their hot tub outside sooo nice! its like built into the concrete and stuff...so cool! 

friday me and katina went shopping..ahh the malls were ridiculously packed with people...but they had really good stores..they had a forever 21 down there and all stores like charlotte russe and h&m..when i move out there ill definitly have some good stores to shop at :) then we went to see bill's warehouse/office where harry's going to work in february :( i dont want him to leave but its REALLY good money out there..so whatever will benefit us in the future..they showed us the slums and we got lunch at some brazilian buffet...it was alright..they came around with meat on sticks and i tried fried bananas lol then we bought bill and katina a water bubbler thing for their house...then we just ordered pizza and called it a night!

saturday we went to breakfast(they served fruit with everything and it was healthy, no grease)..then we went to santa fe and shopped around...it reminded me of a newburyport or a rockport with stores lined up on the streets and basically tourist attractions...like some weird staircase in a church we saw that shouldnt be able to hold weight on it but people can walk on it...i got my mom some turquoise earrings and my dad a dreamcatcher thingy...then bills parents took us out to dinner..his mom was drunk so it was a good time lol

sunday we went to breakfast in some ghetto place and bums were walking in and asking for money...it was a little weird...and then we went shopping in old town albuquerque...kinda a smaller version of santa fe but it was still fun to walk around...i got a cold stone cake batter ice cream :) love it! and then for dinner we went to olive garden because we love it there and plus theres none around here!

and then monday we just woke up, went to the only dunks in the city (by the way, they didnt have ice for ice coffee AND you had to put your own cream and sugar in the coffee!!!) starbucks was everywhere instead of dunks...and then we had the plane at 9am and got home around 7pm..long day!!

but it was soooo much fun! they had chick-fil-a drive thru's, panda express drive thru (chinese food ew), whataburger drive thrus haha, carl's jr drive thru, and best of all they had SONIC everywhere!!! all the roads are like highways and mountains are everywhere! its so pretty :) the houses are all stucco and one story and the mansions there are gorgeous!

we met bill's aunt and uncle and they have not just one house, but FOUR HOUSES!! they even have one in vail,colorado where all the famous people go to go skiing!! AND they have live in maids, cooks, and gardeners!!! thats so crazy!

well thats the trip and ill be going back there in march and probably spending the whole summer out there since harry's moving there in february!i can't wait :)

i leave for new mexico in 2 days! this is crazy! i havent even finished packing and i have no idea what to wear thanksgiving day! ahh so crazy...

on the other hand...my dad is in salem hospital right now because he has cellulitis..its a leg infection..he can't really walk because his leg is swollen and painful..he was suppose to be coming out today but they're keeping him in even longer now...he probably will still be in there for thanksgiving :( i feel bad leaving my mom home, but she told me to go to new mexico with harry..if it worsens up before tomorrow night i will definitley be cancelling my plane tickets...

i saw harry potter yesterday with harry...it was really good!! but for some reason i thought the prisoner of azkaban was scarier than this one! those dementors are definitly freaky looking!

i hope these new mexico people serve turkey on thanksgiving and like mashed potatoes... there is no way im eating like pigs feet or whatever crazy food they eat out there...ill be eating bread and butter if thats the case 

harry's christmas list:
-buddha statue
-scented matches
-GNC gift card
-american eagle jacket
-swiss army watch
(yeah he doesn't read this thing)

im going to get him some shirts and that's probably about it...maybe a movie too?? family guy dvd's!! hahah stewie is awesome!

the malls are so crazy already! why is christmas such a stressful hectic holiday??? 

i got my mom an annalee doll for christmas :) she loves those things and i got it from the real store in new hampshire! i dont know what to get my dad yet..probably just something sports related..

ill get harry's parents a restaurant gift certificate...probably to capone's because that's where us 6 usually get dinner when we all meet up :) 

my mom always makes my nana a calendar with my huge face on it...really who wants to stare at my face for a WHOLE YEAR??? haha i have no idea!!! 

well my mom just walked by me at work and told me to get off of this and do some real work...so i guess ill go :)

hmmm what have i been up to...

halloween i just went downtown with sarah and her roomate and her roomates bf and some of his friends from salem... it was alright... harry couldnt come down because he had class that night

i cant believe its already halfway through november and first semester of sophmore year is almost over!! soo weird!!

i went to danvers high with sam last night because fenwick was suppose to compete in the cheering competition but they didnt send in papers in time? so they couldnt? but it was still fun...we went to applebees too mmmm!!!

on another note...harry might have to move down to new mexico for a couple of months because hes going to start working for katinas boyfriend bill selling like packaging machines (bill makes a shitload of money doing that)...bill even made him business cards already!!.. but that wont be until like february-march... but still its going to suck pretty much..and obviously i cant just up and leave and go down there with him?? i have to finish school and theres nooooo way neen will let me move out there until im done with school...which is still 2 more years..

we're going down to new mexico in two weeks for thanksgiving.. hes going to go to the plant bill works at and learn stuff then, and we're probably going to go to santa fe and alburquerque (or however you spell it lol)it should be fun..but we need to stop in cinncinnatti ohio and then take another plane to new mexico which will be a pain in the butt but i guess it will be alright...and we're flying out of manchester,nh airport?? 5am in the morning too!! hmm this should be interesting...

haven't been doing too much lately...

last weekend me and harry just went out to dinner, went to his friend don's house, saw doom and then sunday we just went to gold's and i did hw while he watched football all day...fun times

schools going pretty good... the classes are pretty easy so thats good...yesterday i was suppose to have a business ethics test at 7am and we're all sitting in the class and this lady comes in and is like he had a fire emergency no class..like wtf?? i woke up so early for nothing and i hung around for 3 hours before my next 10am class...then i get to my marketing class and i find out my business law teacher isnt here and i was suppose to have a quiz in that class too!! sooo weird!! i havent missed any classes once this semester and yesterday would have been the perfect day off!

wednesday i had class 12:30-5 so i went tanning before, met sarah before class just to hang out for a little...and then i met with her and amanda for dinner..every wednesday nights are now officially girls nights :)

this semester is definitly going by fast...its going to be halloween on monday (heading downtown like usual with harry and some of the girls) and then thanksgiving will be here!! which means flying down to new mexico for 6 days wooooo! vacation time :) and then the semester will be over! then CHRISTMASSSSS! and harry is staying at our house because cindy and charlie are going to new mexico for christmas for 2 weeks! so for the first time i have someone to open up presents with :)

andddd me and harry are saving money in an account so we can go away next summer :) soooooo pumped!!!! maybe jamaica or bahamas or aruba...either one would be awesome!

went to new hampshire last weekend..

we were going to go up on friday night but it was really crappy out so we didn't... harry's parents took us all out to dinner at Maggio's in revere? i think...and then we went to the movies and saw two for the money... it was alright, some parts dragged on and im not into the whole "sports betting" deal...

saturday we left for new hampshire around 11... we went for a ride to some shops but it was pouring so we left and went out to eat again hahah...this time we got chinese food and it was alright... they had stale fortune cookies WTFFF

ended up going to bed really early and waking up really early the next day... we met up with diana and artie and all of them and went to this apple picking farm... it was raining so we just bought apples that were already packaged...and got some cider and apple donuts MMMMM...then we headed over to the annalee shop and some furniture store...everyone was hungry (like usual) so we went to hart's turkey farm..sooo good!!! i ended up falling asleep at 7 that night lol

monday charlie made breakfast and then we drove up to harrys uncles house who lives near salem, new hampshire... his grandmother made us soup and we just all sat around and talked.. i played barbies and polly pocket with his little girl cousins hahah it was fun though!!!

i had a midterm in marketing tuesday and a quiz in law... ewww but i think i did ok... and tuesday night we went to angelica's for katina's 25th birthday... it was fun! cindy's whole side was there and sam went so it was fun! 

friday night we're going out to eat with harry, his parents, my parents, and katina and bill...it should be fun :) and saturday im going shopping at the wrentham outlets!!! katina and bill leave sunday and then its back to the old routine next week...

bill might fly me and harry down to new mexico for new years!!!!!!! so excited...free airfare woooo :)

so im sitting at work like usual on my friday afternoons...

just went to get some crackers and redbull with sam across the street! its sooooo nice out today! too bad this weekend is going to SUCK and its going to RAIN THE ENTIRE TIME! booo

but anyways...katina and bill came in last night and we went to the topsfield fair with them and harry's parents...so much fun!! i got a corndog and ice cream lol what a fatty...i didnt get apple crisp for the first time in like 4 years...we went to see the animals and some like horse racing thing? idk..hick stuff basically...harry won me a monkey and an alligator ( but i told him to keep the alligator because it was ugly oops haha ) no rides this year...the zipper was always eventful haha saw the midget lady again! it was a different lady but she was still wicked creepy! 

classes sucked this week...like usual.. probably bombed my weather and climate test...awesome..

harry had work off on wednesday so we just hung out and got breakfast...and then we went to look for a black kitty for katina's birthday!! but we had no luck :( i saw a lot of cute kittens though and i want another one!! toetoe needs a friend :)

were going up new hampshire tonight after the gym... it should be a good weekend! if there is no drama...because whenever we go up there it always seems like their is constant drama...and not even just with the kids its the adults mostly! but we'll probably go to the friedburg fair, shop at some outlets (i need some new jeans/black pants!!) and get dinner at the best restaurant in the world...OLIVE GARDEN!!!! mmmmmm love it!! 

...lost 12lbs back into my clothes again :)

this weekend was fun :)

friday i got my hair done...instead of getting lowlights i decided on lighter highlights because im too pale to get dark hair...it just wouldnt look right..then friday night me, harry, sarah, and ruth went to the cheesecake factory...their bf's had to work and sam went up camp so it was just us 4...it was fun though :) we just talked and laughed and watched the red sox game...then at the end the people sang happy birthday and wrote it in chocolate on my cheesecake plate mmm hahah harry got me a watch, some body lotion stuff, and a victoria secret gift card haha sarah got me a victoria secret gift card too!! after that, me harry and sarah went to harry's friend bills house and saw brad, sean, nicole, jimmy, and steve...that was fun :) amanda gave me a nice bday call at 12:30 hahah thanks amanda! hope those embry-riddle pilots are treating you good! :)

saturday i worked til 12:30 and then went to golds with harry...after that we went to brad's house for his birthday slash going-away-to-the-army party...we ended up at this kid blodgett's house and just hung out...met some nice people and sat around a little bonfire thing...we should do this more often!

sunday harry woke me up early and took me to marias for breakfast...then we headed to burlington mall so i could waste my birthday money on clothes..figures i dont buy any clothes haha i got a purse from aldo (its bronze or copper?) and has sequin things on it..and then i got this lip gloss at sephora and bad gal eyeliner from filenes..then we met up with my parents and his parents at rainforest cafe mmm i got sang to again (ew i hate that its so embarrasing...then we went to the hospital because harry's cousin david's gf sarah had her baby boy :) he is the cutest baby i have ever seen! i held him for like a half an hour and he just laid there sound asleep!!! sooo cute!

2 weather and climate tests this week...ahhh shoot me! one is for the actual class and the other one is for the lab...i hope their easy!

katina and bill come up from new mexico on thursday...i cant wait! it should be fun! i havent seen her basically since april..we're going up new hampshire next weekend for the holiday and we're going to the friedburg fair and apple picking and all that fun fall stuff :) i hope the leaves are all changing colors up there!! we'll probably spend a day in boston and go to the wrentham outlets to go shopping! woooo! they leave october 16 so it should be a good time :) and then me and harry go to new mexico to see them for thanksgiving and we get to see their new house!! 

today is officially 8 months <3 i love my lulu :)

ok so this week went by kinda fast...thank god!

i had a law test (did probably really bad..) and then i had a communications and a weather & climate quiz...which hopefully made up for my law grade...

went to the mall wednesday night with sarah again lol i got a pink purse from the gap and it has cute red cherries in it! i love it! and i got a pink cordoroy skirt from american eagle and a white tank top thats tight on top then flows out kind of...only $6 for the tank!! and the skirt was on sale too! haha bargain shopping is key

other than that school is good :) one person is bugging me ALOT and i just want to punch her in the face, but theres nothing i can really do about that...maybe someone else can punch her in the face for me :)

tonight is cheesecake factory MMMMMMM :) sooo good! 19 finallyy! i think its just going to end up being me, harry, sarah, ruth, chris, and larry...this birthday needs to jump 2 years ahead sooo i can be 21 and actually go out with harry and his other friends to bars and just have a good time...

im also getting my hair done today at 11:30! im kinda nervous, because 1.) im getting lowlights instead of highlights, kind of a chestnut auburn color and 2.) im going to try and go for the long side swept bang kind of look. it better come out good!!! if not then....that will just suck and i will never get a haircut on my birthday ever again...

i love my lulu and its going to be 8 months monday awwww <3 he makes me smile alot :)

loooooong week

classes seemed like they lasted forever this week, and i felt like i was rushing around everywhere all the time...

stupid bookstore sent me the wrong book which i was suppose to get "the next business day" but didnt get it until 2 weeks later...stupid people who work there..they send the book late AND its wrong...what is so hard about working at a BOOKSTORE?!? 

other then that...school is alright...my ethics teacher is a nutcase who never stays on track and seems like hes always speaking a different language..my weather & climate teacher is bald on the top of his head but has brown hair around the sides and back? what a goofball..and he wears his pants up to his belly button...my marketing teacher is boring but we get to watch movies :) one had a janet jackson music video in it hahah my law teacher is pretty easy, shes young and she outlines so you never have to take notes YESSSS...my lab teacher is pretty easy, and my communications class is fun because we listen to music and talk about nothing :)

wednesday night i went to the mall with sarah and ruth...got some khakis at american eagle :) i dont know why, but im just sick of jeans so i decided on a good old pair of khakis..we saw nikki at express! and then we went home...

next friday night cheesecake factory at burlington mall!! soo excited :) finally 19!! one more year til the 20's! thats sooo weird! but cool too i guess!! 

on another note... neen is a bitch... she has been and always will be one :)

started school last wednesday...

classes this semester:

tuesday/thursday
*business ethics: 7-8:15
*weather & climate: 10-11:15

There may be days when you get up in the morning and things aren't the way you had hoped they would be. That's when you have to tell yourself that things will get better. There are times when people disappoint you and let you down, but those are the times when you must remind yourself to trust your own judgements and opinions, and to keep your life focused on believing in yourself and all that you are capable of. There will be challenges to face and changes to make in your life, and it is up to you to accept them. Constantly keep yourself headed in the right direction for you. It may not be easy at times, but in those times of struggle you will find a stronger sense of who you are, and you will also see yourself developing into the person yoy have always wanted to be. Life is a journey through time, filled with many choices; each of us will experience life in our own special way. So when the days come that are filled with frustration and unexpected responsibilities, remember to believe in yourself and all that you want your life to be, because the challenges and changes will only help you to find the dreams that you know are meant to come true for you.

went to new hampshire this weekend with harry...

we got up to the camp around 6ish friday night and just ended up playing cards and watching the red sox game...

saturday we woke up really early and went and got breakfast at the barnstead country store..soo good :) harry docked his jet ski in the lake in back of sam's camp and we took it out for a little ride...that night we went to weirs beach with everyone and just walked around, ate some food, and went to this sketchy tatoo place... i got some flavored honey sticks mmm soo good! and harry got me a pink ring :) we watched some fireworks and then went back to the camp...

sunday we just hung out because it was raining all day... for lunch we went to some buffet that had chinese, japanese, italian food...it was actually pretty good...then we went and saw the longest yard..we were tired so we watched titanic then went to bed...

yesterday we woke up early..got breakfast again at the country store...and then cleaned up, had a cookout at sam's camp with everyone..and got home around 6ish and there was no traffic :)

all in all pretty good weekend, but i wish the weather was nicer
